# When set to false, the software considers the PLL clock output to be 
	# electrically isolated from the input-side reference clock, and creates 
	# the output clock with an idealized transition.  You can use set_annotated_transition 
	# to customize the output clock transition.    When set to true,  delay 
	# calculation of all enabled arcs to the PLL clock output will be used 
	# to compute the transition. If no driving arcs are available in the model 
	# or if they are disabled, the same idealized transition will be used.